# Feature Toggle Testing

Always use `FakeFeatureToggleFactory` — never mocks or custom fakes.

```kotlin
private val fakeFeature = FakeFeatureToggleFactory.create(MyFeature::class.java)

@SuppressLint("DenyListedApi")
@Test
fun `when enabled`() {
    fakeFeature.self().setRawStoredState(Toggle.State(enable = true))
    // assert enabled behavior
}

@SuppressLint("DenyListedApi")
@Test
fun `when disabled`() {
    fakeFeature.self().setRawStoredState(Toggle.State(enable = false))
    // assert disabled behavior
}
```

- Test both enabled and disabled states
- For sub-features: also test with the main feature (`self()`) disabled
- Set sub-feature state: `fakeFeature.enableFilters().setRawStoredState(Toggle.State(enable = true))`
- Add `testImplementation project(':feature-toggles:feature-toggles-test')` to dependencies